Your code is correct but you simply need to move the buffer before the parallel call. Like this:
```java

    Flux.range(1, 10)
                .buffer(3)
                .parallel()
                .runOn(Schedulers.parallel())
                .doOnNext(number -&gt; {
                    sleepMillis(1000);
                    System.out.println(number + &quot;Thread : &quot; + Thread.currentThread().getName());
                })
                .doOnNext(number -&gt; {
                    sleepMillis(1000);
                    System.out.println(&quot;Processing element: &quot; + number);
                })
                .doOnNext(batch -&gt; {
                    sleepMillis(1000);
                    System.out.println(&quot;Batch: &quot; + batch);
                })
                .sequential() 
                .blockLast();
```

By calling sleepMillis(1000) you will be able to see the parallel processing every step of the way.

In addition, by calling, Thread.currentThread().getName(), you can see the thread name which will confirm parallel processing.

