 - You are scanning the user&#39;s input just once, in other words, all the jokes will be displayed at once.
 - *randomNumber* keeps increasing **with no verification**, which results in *java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException*.
 - Have a chance of your *randomNumber* being &#39;4&#39;, which will make just 1 joke be displayed.

To solve all problems, I do this way:

```java
public class Main {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// Jokes dynamic list
		List&lt;String&gt; jokes = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
		jokes.add(&quot;You can only get spoiled milk from a pampered cow&quot;);
		jokes.add(&quot;I hate Russian dolls—they&#39;re so full of themselves&quot;);
		jokes.add(&quot;I have a fear of speed bumps, but I am slowly getting over it&quot;);
		jokes.add(&quot;A plateau is the highest form of flattery&quot;);
		jokes.add(&quot;I have many jokes about rich kids, but sadly, none of them work&quot;);

		// Randomize
		Collections.shuffle(jokes);

		// Scanner
		Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);

		// Random generator
		Random random = new Random();

        // Loop
		while (true) {
			// Verify list
			if (jokes.isEmpty()) {
				System.out.println(&quot;End of jokes&quot;);
				break;
			}

			// Ask user
			System.out.println(&quot;Want to hear a joke? Yes/No&quot;);

			// User answer
			String userResponse = scanner.nextLine();

			// Verify
			if (userResponse.equals(&quot;Yes&quot;)) {
				// Number
				int randomNumber = random.nextInt(jokes.size());

				// Display joke
				System.out.println(jokes.get(randomNumber));

				// Remove joke from list
				jokes.remove(randomNumber);
			} else if (userResponse.equals(&quot;No&quot;)) {
				// Stop loop
				break;
			}
		}

		// Close scanner
		scanner.close();
	}
}
