&gt; How to capture heap dump while running azure pipeline ?

One practice is to using [jmap][1] command-line tool on running the pipeline to capture a heap dump in binary format and save it to a file (heapdumpreport.bin).
Replace the `PID` with the process ID of your Java application, the `sas-token`, `name-of-your-container` and `storage-account-name` tags with proper values.



    - script: |
        jmap -dump:format=b,file=heapdumpreport.bin &lt;PID&gt;
        azcopy copy heapdumpreport.bin &quot;https://&lt;storage-account-name&gt;.blob.core.windows.net/&lt;name-of-your-container&gt;/heapdumpreport.bin?sas-token&quot;
      displayName: &#39;Heap Dump Report&#39;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Which this script we used `azcopy` command  to upload the heap dump into your storage account using an SAS token.


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/troubleshoot/tooldescr014.html

